    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Society Worth Shielding</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>William Guy letter on June 23 article questions whether United States can afford missile defense system</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report that proponents insist that ''if the United States has the money and technology to develop a missile defense, it should do so'' (front page, June 23).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>You report that proponents insist that ''if the United States has the money and technology to develop a missile defense, it should do so'' (front page, June 23).</p>
        <p>But do we really have the money? This is the question that never gets honestly considered. Yes, we will manage to foot the bill in billions of dollars for ''Star Wars,'' but will we  then be better off as a society than we would have been if we had provided insurance for the millions of our citizens who now have to face health care bills on their own, or if we had invested those billions in our education system?</p>
        <p>Missile defense becomes an oxymoron unless we have a just society to defend.</p>
        <p>WILLIAM GUY  Pittsburgh, June 23, 2000</p>
      </block>
